&lt;p&gt;Ir was ritten by &lt;strong&gt;Homer&lt;/strong&gt;, the same poet who wrote &lt;em&gt;The Iliad&lt;/em&gt;.  It was composed around &lt;strong&gt;8th century BCE&lt;/strong&gt; in ancient Greece.&lt;br&gt;
It is an &lt;strong&gt;epic poem&lt;/strong&gt; with &lt;strong&gt;24 books&lt;/strong&gt; (sections), written in &lt;strong&gt;dactylic hexameter&lt;/strong&gt;, Contains &lt;strong&gt;over 12,000 lines&lt;/strong&gt; of poetry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Odyssey&lt;/em&gt; is about &lt;strong&gt;human resilience, wisdom, and the longing for home&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
